OL,3,CJersey's Government to introduce
OL,4,Cmodern slavery legislation
OL,6,FThe government says it will work
OL,7,Falongside people with lived
OL,8,Fexperience, law enforcement agencies,
OL,9,Femployers, and charities to make sure
OL,10,Fthe new law is practical, balanced and
OL,11,Fbased on evidence.
OL,13,FIt adds that the legislation will be
OL,14,Fdeveloped through careful and
OL,15,Finclusive consultation.
OL,17,FThe Minister for Justice and Home
OL,18,FAffairs, Mary Le Hegarat, says: "Cases
OL,19,Fin Jersey may be rare, but even one
OL,20,Fcase of exploitation is one too many.
