OL,6,F"If anyone were held in conditions
OL,7,Famounting to modern slavery, it is
OL,8,Fvery likely that alternative charges
OL,9,Fcould be made under existing laws,
OL,10,Fpotentially related to the unlawful
OL,11,Fdetention of a person, or their
OL,12,Ftreatment under employment law, and
OL,13,Fany reports of that nature would be
OL,14,Fvery thoroughly investigated.
OL,16,F"It is important to stress that
OL,17,Flegislation is not the only work we
OL,18,Fcan do on this.
